issue.title: lit-html/is-server.js cannot be found caused by missing version for lit
issue.body:
### Describe the bug

Getting this error:

Webpack build failed with errors:
ERROR in ../node_modules/.pnpm/lit@2.4.0/node_modules/lit/index.js
Module not found: Error: Can't resolve 'lit-html/is-server.js' in '....\node_modules\.pnpm\lit@2.4.0\node_modules\lit'
 @ ../node_modules/.pnpm/lit@2.4.0/node_modules/lit/index.js 1:87-122 1:87-122
 @ ../node_modules/@vaadin/flow-frontend/@f0rce/lit-ace/lit-ace.js
 @ ../target/frontend/generated-flow-imports.js

Caused by:

There is no version provided (in package.json) for "lit" so the newest version (lit 2.4.0) is used.
In lit 2.4.0 index.js the file lit-html/is-server.js should be load but doesnt exists because lit-html is provided with version 1.4.1 (in package.json) but is-server.js exists only from version 2.4.0.

### Expected-behavior

Versions should work together, lit should be explicit provided with version 2.3.0 (so as it is in newest vaadin version).

### Reproduction

Allways

### System Info

Windows, Vaadin 14.8.20, Google Chrome 107.0.5304.88

- re-uses the existing date-fns parsing and formatting logic using the created pattern, removes custom parsing and formatting logic for locale-based mode
- adds additional check for unsupported locales and falls back to `en-US` if a valid pattern could not be created
- restructure locale-based ITs to use a single date picker that allows changing the locale

## Type of change

- Refactoring

issue.body:
## Description

Changes the date picker connector to use date-fns for locale-based parsing and formatting instead of implementing custom logic.
- creates a date-dns pattern from the output of `Date.toLocaleDateString(locale)` instead of creating a regex for parsing
- re-uses the existing date-fns parsing and formatting logic using the created pattern, removes custom parsing and formatting logic for locale-based mode
- adds additional check for unsupported locales and falls back to `en-US` if a valid pattern could not be created
- restructure locale-based ITs to use a single date picker that allows changing the locale

## Type of change

- Refactoring
